PHONE REVENUE DECREASED $4.2 BILLION OR 56%, AS WE SOLD 13.8 MILLION MICROSOFT LUMIA (LUMIA) PHONES AND 75.5 MILLION OTHER PHONES IN FISCAL YEAR 2016, COMPARED WITH

36.8 MILLION AND 126.8 MILLION SOLD, RESPECTIVELY, IN FISCAL YEAR 2015. SURFACE REVENUE INCREASED $486 MILLION OR 13%, PRIMARILY DRIVEN BY THE RELEASE OF SURFACE PRO 4 AND SURFACE BOOK IN THE SECOND QUARTER OF FISCAL YEAR 2016, AS WELL AS

THE RELEASE OF SURFACE 3 IN THE FOURTH QUARTER OF FISCAL YEAR 2015, OFFSET IN PART BY A DECLINE IN REVENUE FROM SURFACE PRO 3. DEVICES REVENUE INCLUDED AN UNFAVORABLE FOREIGN CURRENCY IMPACT OF APPROXIMATELY 3%.

