OEM NON-PRO REVENUE INCREASED 7%, OUTPERFORMING THE CONSUMER PC MARKET, DRIVEN BY A HIGHER MIX OF PREMIUM LICENSES SOLD. WINDOWS PHONE LICENSING REVENUE DECREASED 64%, DRIVEN BY THE RECOGNITION OF DEFERRED REVENUE IN FISCAL YEAR 2015 FROM WINDOWS

PHONE 8. WINDOWS REVENUE INCLUDED AN UNFAVORABLE FOREIGN CURRENCY IMPACT OF APPROXIMATELY 2%.

